      "writtenOn": "2016-07-27T17:10:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this is a very bad decision (maybe not yours -- was this pre-existing behavior?)  The dashes in -debug-\u003c...\u003e (to me) indicating that the things they separate are to be considered as one composite joined thing.  Having a comma-separated list as one of these joined things seems to me Very Wrong.  I have never seen a command-line interface that worked this way (where \",\" bound tighter than \"-\", if you want to look at it that way.)  Just to be sure, I asked one other person if they found the example I gave odd or normal, and they found it odd.\n\nIs the -debug-\u003ctag(s)\u003e form really necessary?  Who would we break if we just eliminated it, allowing only the \"-debug \u003ctags\u003e\" form?",
